Here's the problem:
No matter what verb I type into my text adventure game, the response is &quot;I can't see that.&quot;
Whether it's trying to pick up a key, or examine the ground, the game gives the same response. I don't know what to do so please help!

If you are working offline, the way to do a smell command is this:

Create a new command. In the first box type [i:3rr0loit]smell[/i:3rr0loit], and in the second [i:3rr0loit]smellcmd[/i:3rr0loit]. In the third, click on the ninth icon, code view, and paste this in:
[code:3rr0loit]if (HasString(player&#46;parent, &quot;smell&quot;)) {
  msg(player&#46;parent&#46;smell)
}
else {
  msg(&quot;You smell nothing much here&#46;&quot;)
}[/code:3rr0loit]
Any room with a smell, go to the attributes tab, create a new attribute called [i:3rr0loit]smell[/i:3rr0loit], and type the appropriate text in.
